Syntax: FORBID <ADD> <registered nickname> <reason>
        FORBID <REM> <id>
        FORBID LIST 
     
You can ban the usage of a nickname on the network by using the 
FORBID ADD command. The service will unregister the nickname and then
place a jupe on the nickname. The reason will be displayed in the
nickname's userinfo. This is done using the FORBID ADD command.
      
You can remove a forbidden nickname by using the FORBID REM command,
or list all forbidden nickname with the FORBID LIST command.
   
SEE ALSO:
  INFO 
